description: The reveal of Mobile Space System's first industrial vessel was met with no small amount of confusion. Sporting three Miura intake regulators and a spacious cargo bay in MMS' own "orange way" interior design, many speculated that the Columbus could never be a cost-effective investment. True to expectations the model never saw a wide-spread use, but the lucky few crews that got to work on board one of these ships have had nothing but praise for it.
